  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add wood ear mushrooms and garlic. Stir-fry for about 5 minutes until mushrooms are tender.",
    "Mix Dijon mustard with soy sauce to make the tangy sauce, then pour it into the mushroom mixture.",
    "Stir well to combine. Add Worcestershire Sauce, reduce heat to low, and let cook for another 2-3 minutes or until slightly thickened.",
    "Garnish with thyme if desired before serving.",
    "Serve hot as a side dish or over rice."
